# 6. Design Principles

The architecture follows several software engineering principles.

## Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)

Each class performs one task.

Example:

* TeamService manages teams.
* ScoreService manages scores.

---

## Open/Closed Principle (OCP)

Components should be open for extension but closed for modification.

New functionality should be added through additional services rather than modifying existing ones.

---

## Liskov Substitution Principle (LSP)

Future implementations should allow service implementations to be replaced without affecting dependent components.

---

## Interface Segregation Principle (ISP)

Interfaces should expose only the operations required by their clients.

---

## Dependency Inversion Principle (DIP)

High-level components should depend on abstractions rather than concrete implementations.

